  "short-title": "24-1",
  "desc": "This major is designed to provide familiarity with the history and current status of the main problems in epistemology, metaphysics, and ethics; mastery of some of the technical skills requisite for advanced work in philosophy; facility at independent philosophical study; and work at an advanced level in an allied field. A relatively large amount of unrestricted elective time is available so that students can devise programs suited to individual needs and interests.\n\nNo more than four of the total number of philosophy subjects for the major may be introductory philosophy subjects. At least three of the total number of philosophy courses must be at the 200 level or above."
